Title : Project Report: Deadlock Detection and Recovery Toolkit


# Project Overview:-
 A deadlock occurs when two or more processes are stuck waiting for resources held by
 each other, causing the system to freeze and halt execution. Traditional deadlock detection
 methods rely on static algorithms such as Wait-For Graphs, Resource Allocation Matrices, and
 Banker's Algorithm, but these approaches struggle in dynamic and large-scale systems, especially 
 cloud and distributed environments where resource usage changes rapidly. The Deadlock Detection
 and Recovery Toolkit System aims to intelligently monitor process behavior and resource
 allocation using machine learning models. Instead of detecting deadlocks after they occur,
 this system focuses on predictive detection, where patterns, anomalies, and historical data 
 are analyzed to identify potential deadlocks before they impact performance.


#Goals of the Project :- 
 .Detect deadlocks in real-time with higher accuracy compared to traditional algorithms.

 .Predict potential deadlocks using machine learning models (e.g., classification, anomaly detection).

 .Improve overall system reliability and reduce performance degradation due to blocked processes. 

 .Provide visualization tools and alerts to system administrators for better decision-making.

 .Integrate traditional OS-level monitoring Project Scope

